# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next UD-Q4_K_XL on 2x R9700 (MACHINE=r9700-dual).
#
# Sourced by run-vulkan.sh AFTER models/qwen3-coder-next-q4.env and BEFORE
# profiles/r9700-dual/default.env.
#
# Target: the model's native 256K context, all weights in VRAM across the pair.
# KV math (verified 2026-07-17): only 12 of 48 layers are full attention with
# 2 KV heads x head_dim 256 -> 12,288 KV elements/token (~24 KiB f16, ~12.75 KiB
# q8_0). The 36 DeltaNet layers keep a small constant F32 state, not KV. The old
# comments here overestimated KV ~2x, which is why V used to be squeezed to q4_0
# -- unnecessary; V is back to the launcher's q8_0 default (matching K keeps the
# fused Vulkan flash-attn path; quantized V requires -fa, which the launcher
# sets).
#   weights (UD-Q4_K_XL)            46.2 GiB
#   KV @ 262,144 tok, q8_0 K+V       3.2 GiB
#   compute buffers @ ubatch 512    ~1.5 GiB per-GPU-small
#   ------------------------------------------
#   total                          ~51 GiB / ~62 GiB VRAM  (comfortable)
# If load OOMs anyway: drop UBATCH to 256 first, then CTX_SIZE.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=262144}"
: "${UBATCH:=512}"
